      "amount": "4 tbsp"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a large pan over medium heat.",
    "Add garlic and chili garlic sauce, sauté for about 1 minute.",
    "Stir in soy sauce, tomato paste, lime juice, vinegar, sugar, and cayenne pepper. Cook until slightly thickened.",
    "Gradually add water, stirring continuously to prevent sticking.",
    "Bring the mixture to a simmer, then reduce heat to low.",
    "Add beef pieces and cook for about 5 minutes or until meat is browned on all sides.",
    "Season with salt and black pepper as needed.",
    "Serve hot over rice."
